;; NOTA records are positional. Type, then fields, no keywords.
;; The `(key value)` shape from Lisp/Clojure/JSON is not NOTA.
;; If you're sketching a new NOTA record, read skills/nota-design.md first.
;;
;; tier values (fourth positional field below):
;;   apex      — read once; recognise everywhere
;;   keystroke — applies on every keystroke and every report
;;   topic     — consulted when the topic comes up
;;   mechanism — procedural; consulted when the named mechanism is in play

[
  (Role operator skills/operator.md Apex
    [Implementation as craft. The discipline an agent brings when the work is landing code.])
  (Role designer skills/designer.md Apex
    [Architecture as craft. What designer specifies; what operator implements against.])
  (Role schema-designer skills/schema-designer.md Apex
    [Specialized designer lane: the schema stack and contract shapes. nota/schema-next/schema-rust-next grammar, signal-* wire contracts, rkyv round-trip, schema-help introspection. Pairs with schema-operator.])
  (Role system-operator skills/system-operator.md Apex
    [OS / platform / deploy craft.])
  (Role system-maintainer skills/system-maintainer.md Apex
    [Crayon OS and Logic maintenance, debugging, updates, and deploys across hosts.])
  (Role poet skills/poet.md Apex
    [Prose as craft.])
  (Role editor skills/editor.md Apex
    [Source-grounded research, quotation, and synthesis as craft.])
  (Role assistant skills/assistant.md Apex
    [Personal-affairs support for the psyche.])
  (Role counselor skills/counselor.md Apex
    [Personal-affairs advisory for the psyche, working with the assistant lane.])

  (Architecture component-triad skills/component-triad.md Apex
    [Daemon + thin CLI + signal-* contract. Signal/Nexus/SEMA runtime triad and async mail flow.])
  (Architecture structural-forms skills/structural-forms.md Apex
    [A language is a set of structural macros kept as data; grammar is a type, match by shape. The StructuralMacroNode derive shape vocabulary; positional schema struct syntax with the key.TypeReference differentiator; pipe-parenthesis generics and pipe-brace traits/impls; the dimensional principle (role is type, no two same-type fields, repetition is a keyed collection, newtype-per-role); streams and families are positional special forms, not structs.])
  (Architecture contract-repo skills/contract-repo.md Topic
    [Wire-contract crate discipline. Six-verb spine; signal_channel! macro; layered-effect pattern.])
  (Architecture micro-components skills/micro-components.md Topic
    [When to create a new crate; family-of-micro-components pattern; kernel-extraction triggers.])
  (Architecture actor-systems skills/actor-systems.md Topic
    [Dense actor topology. Schema-root actors; async mail objects; supervised state-bearing actors.])
  (Architecture architectural-truth-tests skills/architectural-truth-tests.md Topic
    [Tests that catch architectural drift, not just regression.])
  (Architecture engine-analysis skills/engine-analysis.md Topic
    [How to analyze daemon/engine internals — the planes-and-actors lens.])
  (Architecture engine-report skills/engine-report.md Topic
    [Standard engine situation reports: component ledgers, code/schema/generated size, interfaces, signatures, runtime paths, witnesses, and introspection tools.])
  (Architecture language-design skills/language-design.md Topic
    [Language-design discipline. Closed enums; structural beauty over ad-hoc strings; branches/leaves vocabulary for typed-record trees.])
  (Architecture library skills/library.md Topic
    [Library-vs-daemon split. When to extract a library crate from a daemon.])
  (Architecture subscription-lifecycle skills/subscription-lifecycle.md Topic
    [Subscription close-vs-retract semantics. Token-keyed cleanup.])

  (Craft abstractions skills/abstractions.md Keystroke
    [Verb belongs to noun. Methods on types; no free helpers when a method would do.])
  (Craft enum-contact-points skills/enum-contact-points.md Apex
    [Engine logic = enum-vs-enum cross-product matching. Name the contact point — nested match or trait — not scattered ad-hoc arms, string predicates, or boolean flag soup.])
  (Craft naming skills/naming.md Keystroke
    [Full English words. The offender table.])
  (Craft secrets skills/secrets.md Keystroke
    [Agents may inspect tokens and other secret values when an authorized task requires plaintext access. Keep visible secrets transient and out of chat, reports, logs, commits, shell traces, the Nix store, fixtures, and checked-in files; prefer gopass, sops-nix, and blind pipe-to-sink handling when enough.])
  (Craft privacy skills/privacy.md Keystroke
    [Private personal-affairs work stays out of public workspace surfaces and privacy Zero Spirit. Elevated Spirit privacy exists, but private repositories remain the conservative default unless the psyche explicitly wants Spirit capture.])
  (Craft workspace-vocabulary skills/workspace-vocabulary.md Topic
    [Canonical glossary for load-bearing workspace terms. main/next, Persona, engine_manager — predecessors, scope, when-to-use.])
  (Craft beauty skills/beauty.md Keystroke
    [Beauty as criterion. Special cases dissolve into the normal case.])
  (Craft push-not-pull skills/push-not-pull.md Keystroke
    [No polling. Subscribe and receive; producers push events.])
  (Craft reporting skills/reporting.md Keystroke
    [When to write a report vs answer in chat. Chat for user; reports for agents.])
  (Workflow report-naming skills/report-naming.md Mechanism
    [Basic report-naming + supersession discipline. Filename convention, -v2/v3 iteration, commit-before-delete. Smaller than skills/reporting.md; every agent needs this.])
  (Workflow workspace-update-report skills/workspace-update-report.md Mechanism
    [Recurring workspace update report variant. Surveys major workspace changes since the previous update report — files changed, intent captures, skill evolution, reports landed/retired, component state. Periodic synthesis the psyche reads to see direction across busy periods.])
  (Workflow versioning skills/versioning.md Keystroke
    [Version bump discipline for code and logic changes. Distinguish component release, wire contract, storage schema, and deploy-slot versions; never leave behavior changes on stale package versions.])
  (Craft typed-records-over-flags skills/typed-records-over-flags.md Keystroke
    [Closed typed records over bool flags. Surface the variant set in the type system.])
  (Craft prose skills/prose.md Topic
    [Prose-craft discipline.])

  (Programming kameo skills/kameo.md Topic
    [Kameo actor-runtime discipline. Lifecycle contract; spawn-in-thread restart trap.])
  (Programming rust-discipline skills/rust-discipline.md Topic
    [Rust craft index. Methods on types; typed errors; no ZST holders.])
  (Programming rust-methods skills/rust/methods.md Topic
    [Methods on schema nouns. No production free functions; async mail flow as object flow.])
  (Programming rust-errors skills/rust/errors.md Topic
    [Typed errors at crate boundary. thiserror; no anyhow at edges.])
  (Programming rust-storage-and-wire skills/rust/storage-and-wire.md Topic
    [redb + rkyv pattern for storage and wire.])
  (Programming rust-parsers skills/rust/parsers.md Topic
    [No hand-rolled parsers. Use winnow or NOTA codec.])
  (Programming rust-crate-layout skills/rust/crate-layout.md Topic
    [Crate layout. Tests in separate files; bin / lib / examples.])
  (Programming nix-discipline skills/nix-discipline.md Topic
    [Nix module structure. Flake conventions; check derivations.])
  (Programming nix-usage skills/nix-usage.md Topic
    [When to use Nix tooling. nix eval / flake show / path-info — not filesystem search.])
  (Programming mermaid skills/mermaid.md Mechanism
    [Mermaid diagram conventions and safe-syntax workarounds.])
  (Programming stt-interpreter skills/stt-interpreter.md Mechanism
    [Speech-to-text interpreter integration notes.])

  (Workflow role-lanes skills/role-lanes.md Mechanism
    [Lane mechanism for main, ordinal, and qualified role lanes.])
  (Workflow architecture-editor skills/architecture-editor.md Mechanism
    [How to edit ARCHITECTURE.md. ARCH never references reports.])
  (Workflow nota-schema-docs skills/nota-schema-docs.md Mechanism
    [Pseudo-NOTA convention for documenting record schemas: angle-bracket placeholders, optional ?, enum |.])
  (Workflow nota-design skills/nota-design.md Topic
    [Canonical NOTA design. The type names the most useful distinction in context; data lives in records, not comments; enums get names, not numbers.])
  (Workflow nota-comments skills/nota-comments.md Topic
    [Code comments as NOTA signal records. (Why ...) opening pattern carries the per-edit rationale; Mind reads code-as-signal; pairs with intent-log for the why-vs-intent boundary.])
  (Workflow jj skills/jj.md Mechanism
    [Jujutsu version-control discipline. Concurrent-agent safety.])
  (Workflow testing skills/testing.md Mechanism
    [All tests in Nix. Pure tests as checks; -test suffix for test-only binaries.])
  (Workflow feature-development skills/feature-development.md Mechanism
    [Feature branches in worktrees, for CODE repos under /git only — NOT primary. Multi-repo arc coordination. On primary everyone works on main directly (record 2585).])
  (Workflow double-implementation-strategy skills/double-implementation-strategy.md Topic
    [Two parallel implementation tracks for a major break, BOTH on branches: operator amalgamates best-of-prototypes toward main; designer iterates the forward-looking design on next / a feature branch. Comparison drives convergence. Anti-drift mechanism. New repos are NOT used — major breaks are branches, a new repo is only for a genuinely new project (Spirit op4b / 53bj, 2026-06-07).])
  (Workflow beads skills/beads.md Mechanism
    [Short-tracked-item discipline. Transitional pre-Persona-mind.])
  (Workflow repository-management skills/repository-management.md Mechanism
    [ghq / gh mechanics for repo work.])
  (Workflow skill-editor skills/skill-editor.md Mechanism
    [How to edit skill files without growing them noisy. Skills never reference reports.])

  (Meta human-interaction skills/human-interaction.md Apex
    [How psyche-facing agents interact with the psyche — load intent-log and spirit-cli fresh, capture intent, handle forwarded prompts, dispatch subagents, run real-world tests, and report back. Must-read for every psyche-facing harness on every session.])
  (Meta autonomous-agent skills/autonomous-agent.md Mechanism
    [When to act vs ask within work. Bead-flow + claim + work + close + release loop. Pairs with human-interaction.md (the psyche-boundary skill) — autonomous-agent is the work-loop discipline.])
  (Meta context-maintenance skills/context-maintenance.md Mechanism
    [Sweep reports and conversation. Migrate substance to permanent homes.])
  (Meta intent-log skills/intent-log.md Topic
    [Record explicit psyche intent through Spirit. Psyche-facing agents keep this fresh before Spirit use; tentative wording is no-capture or ask. Clarifications and corrections target existing records through edit operations rather than additive duplicate Records. Five-kind positional NOTA with closed Domains, certainty, importance, privacy, referents, and justification.])
  (Meta spirit-cli skills/spirit-cli.md Topic
    [How to invoke the deployed Spirit 0.13.0 CLI. RecordRequest shape, maintenance operations, missing ResolveClarification protocol, bare-string canonicality, recursive Domain records, separate certainty and importance, eight-field query shape, justifications, privacy, inline NOTA vs file-path argument, and deployed-source verification.])
  (Meta intent-maintenance skills/intent-maintenance.md Mechanism
    [Sweep the Spirit intent log. Clarification is an edit of an existing target, not another active Record; ResolveClarification folds a mistaken standalone clarification into its clarified targets, then removes or retires the standalone clarification. Supersession protocol; verification against current state; legacy intent files are history.])
  (Meta intent-clarification skills/intent-clarification.md Topic
    [Ask the psyche when intent on a question is unclear, absent, or contradicted. Don't infer intent; ask. Structured options + lean.])
  (Meta repo-intent skills/repo-intent.md Keystroke
    [Per-repo INTENT.md is the FIRST and most important file per repo — canonical agent-context surface of psyche-stated goals, constraints, principles; read on entry before code. Agent-written prose, 100% backed by psyche statements, no inference. Every repo needs one; workspace intent affecting a repo lands in its INTENT.md in the work cycle. Spirit 944 Maximum.])
  (Meta intent-manifestation skills/intent-manifestation.md Mechanism
    [Walk through Spirit records; manifest recorded intent into the right guidance file (ESSENCE / AGENTS / INTENT / skills / per-repo INTENT). Verbatim quotes in italics. Eventually automated by persona-spirit.])
  (Meta keep-working skills/keep-working.md Keystroke
    [Psyche info-injection mid-task is not a stop signal. Keep working unless explicitly told to stop or redirected. Absorb the context, capture any durable intent, and continue; do not drop the work and go passive.])
  (Workflow main-next skills/main-next.md Keystroke
    [Each CODE repo under /git keeps main (operator-owned, integrated line) plus a long-lived next development branch (the designer line). Designer works on next; operator integrates next into main. When main is locked or busy, designer uses next and never blocks. NOT for primary — on primary everyone works on main directly (record 2585). Record 2561.])
  (Workflow main-feature-integration skills/main-feature-integration.md Mechanism
    [Updating code-repo main with new features: start from main, use an operator bookmark until green, test branch families together, rebase if main moved, then land producers before consumers and rerun checks.])
]
